Healiora – Privacy Policy

Last Updated: [Insert Date]

Healiora (“we”, “our”, “us”) is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what data we collect, why we collect it, and how we handle it when you use our services including the Healiora Patient App, Doctor Portal, and Hospital Dashboard.

1. Information We Collect
1.1 Personal Information

We collect the following information when you sign up or use the app:

Name

Email address

Phone number

Date of birth

Gender

Emergency contact details

1.2 Medical Information

If you upload or sync medical records, we may collect:

Prescriptions

Lab reports

Doctor summaries

Any health-related documents you choose to store

1.3 Device & App Usage Data

We automatically collect:

Device model, OS version

IP address

Crash logs, performance data

App interaction data (screens visited, features used)

1.4 Location Information

If you allow it, we may collect precise location for:

SOS emergency alerts

Location-based hospital routing

Location is collected only during active SOS use unless explicitly permitted otherwise.

2. How We Use Your Information

We use your information to:

Provide core features (SOS alerts, medical record storage)

Improve app performance

Communicate with you regarding updates, alerts, or support

Maintain safety and fraud prevention

Comply with legal requirements

We do NOT sell your data.
We never use your medical data for advertising.

3. How We Share Information

We may share information only with:

Emergency Contacts (during SOS activation)

Hospitals/Doctors you explicitly connect with

Service providers (e.g., analytics, cloud storage) bound by confidentiality

Government or law enforcement only when legally required

We do not allow third-party advertising SDKs to access your medical records.

4. Data Storage & Security

We use:

Encrypted data transmission (HTTPS/TLS)

Encrypted data storage for medical files

Restricted internal access to user information

Industry-standard security practices

Despite our efforts, no digital platform is 100% secure, and you use the app at your own risk.

5. Your Rights

You can request to:

Access your data

Update or correct your information

Delete your account

Export your medical records

Email us at: [insert email]

We will respond within 30 days as required by law.

6. Children’s Privacy

Healiora is not intended for users under 13 unless supervised by a legal guardian. We do not knowingly collect data from children.

7. Third-Party Services

The app may integrate:

Cloud storage

Analytics tools

Crash reporting systems

Each service follows its own privacy practices. We ensure none of them receive medical data unless required for core functionality.

8. Permissions We Use

Location (SOS routing)

Storage (upload medical files)

Camera (scan prescriptions, documents)

Contacts (SOS emergency contacts)

Internet (cloud sync, authentication)

We request permissions only when required for core features.

9. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Continued use of the app after changes means you accept the updated version.

10. Contact Us

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact us at:

Email: [insert support email]
Company: Healiora
Address: [insert address]
